    "body": "### Problem\n\nIf you create 2 `extmark`:\n\n1. at row n with some `virt_lines` & `virt_lines_above = false`\n2. directly below at row n + 1 with `conceal_lines = ''` \n \nAs you scroll passed the concealed line it'll cause the lines displayed to be offset.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. `minimal.lua`:\n\n```lua\nvim.opt.conceallevel = 3\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd('BufWinEnter', {\n    callback = function()\n        local ns = vim.api.nvim_create_namespace('test')\n        vim.api.nvim_buf_set_extmark(0, ns, 0, 0, {\n            virt_lines = {\n                { { 'Virtual Line', 'DiffChange' } },\n            },\n            virt_lines_above = false,\n        })\n        vim.api.nvim_buf_set_extmark(0, ns, 1, 0, {\n            conceal_lines = '',\n        })\n    end,\n})\n```\n\n2. `test.txt`:\n\n```text\nLine 1\nLine 2\nLine 3\nLine 4\nLine 5\n```\n\n3. `nvim --clean -u minimal.lua test.txt`\n\n4. Scroll down to the 4th line by pressing `j` 3 times (IMPORTANT this does not happen if you run `3j`, it only happens if you go line by line)\n \n5. Observe that the line above the current one now shows `Line 4` instead of `Line 3` and the `virtual_line` we placed below `Line 1` has disappeared\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nFollowing the steps to reproduce the issue:\n\n| Expected Display | Actual Display |\n| ----------------- | -------------- |\n| <img width=\"178\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/19610a44-da64-4eff-ab1b-eff60b15e52d\" /> | <img width=\"178\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/55caad1f-5066-4e71-a8da-752d9b822e60\" /> |\n\nSince `ghostty` is relatively new I also confirmed the same behavior using `WezTerm` where $Term = `xterm-256color`.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.11.0-dev-1906+g35e5307af2\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNo: I don't believe extmarks exist in vim\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS 15.3.1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nghostty 1.1.2\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-ghostty\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
